---
/**
 * Business Impact Page
 * Industry research on the relationship between web performance and business outcomes.
 */

import AdminLayout from "@/layouts/AdminLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Business Impact";
const pageDescription =
  "How Core Web Vitals affect conversion, revenue, and user engagement — based on published industry research.";
---

<AdminLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  activeSection="business-impact"
>
  <!-- Context note -->
  <div class="mb-8 p-4 bg-(--surface-secondary) border border-(--border-primary) rounded-sm">
    <p class="text-sm text-(--content-meta)">
      This page summarizes published research on the relationship between web performance and business outcomes.
      Once the site has sufficient traffic, real field data will appear on the
      <a href="/admin/performance" class="underline text-(--content-body)">Performance Overview</a> page
      via the Chrome UX Report.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Key findings -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-6">What the Research Shows</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <!-- LCP / Loading -->
      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-4">Loading Speed (LCP)</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Conversion correlation</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Google found that sites loading in 1s convert 3× better than sites loading in 5s</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Revenue lift</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Milliseconds matter: Deloitte found a 0.1s improvement in speed correlated with an 8% increase in conversions for retail sites</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Bounce rate</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Pages that take 3s to load see 32% higher bounce rates vs. 1s pages (Google/SOASTA research)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- INP / Responsiveness -->
      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-4">Responsiveness (INP)</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Perceived quality</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Interactions that respond in under 100ms feel instantaneous to users; delays above 300ms feel sluggish</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Task completion</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Slow interactions increase error rates in checkout and form flows, directly reducing completion rates</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Mobile sensitivity</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Mobile users are more sensitive to input latency than desktop users; INP has larger business impact on mobile</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CLS / Stability -->
      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-4">Visual Stability (CLS)</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Trust and confidence</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Layout shifts cause accidental clicks and erode user trust — especially damaging on product and checkout pages</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Add-to-cart abandonment</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Shifts that move "Add to Cart" buttons cause accidental taps on wrong items, increasing returns and support load</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Search ranking</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">CLS is a Google Search ranking signal — poor CLS can reduce organic traffic</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SEO impact -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-6">Search Ranking Impact</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Core Web Vitals as a ranking signal</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Page Experience update</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Google formally incorporated Core Web Vitals (LCP, INP, CLS) into its search ranking algorithm in 2021 and has continued to increase their weight</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">The "Good" threshold matters</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Google's ranking signal uses the 75th percentile of real-user field data. Passing the "Good" threshold on all three CWV provides a measurable ranking benefit</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Competitive context</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">The ranking benefit is most visible when competing pages in the same niche have poor CWV — fast sites gain relative advantage</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Tracking organic impact</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Google Search Console</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">The "Core Web Vitals" report in Search Console shows how Google categorizes your URLs — use this to identify pages holding back your overall score</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Impressions vs. clicks</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">After improving CWV, watch Search Console for changes in average position and click-through rate on target keywords over 4–8 weeks</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Research references -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-6">Published Research</h2>
    <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
          <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-1">Google / Think with Google</div>
          <div class="text-(--content-meta)">"The Need for Mobile Speed" and "Find out how you stack up to new industry benchmarks" — research on load time and mobile conversion</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
          <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-1">Deloitte / Google "Milliseconds Make Millions"</div>
          <div class="text-(--content-meta)">0.1s mobile speed improvement correlated with 8% conversion increase, 9% increase in average order value for retail</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
          <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-1">web.dev / Chrome team</div>
          <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Case studies from Vodafone, Rakuten, Netzwelt, and others showing measurable business outcomes from CWV improvements</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
          <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-1">HTTP Archive</div>
          <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Annual Web Almanac tracks CWV adoption across millions of sites — useful for industry benchmarking context</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Actionable priorities -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-6">Highest-Impact Priorities</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-green-200 border-l-4 border-l-green-500">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Revenue-critical pages first</h3>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span>Optimize LCP on the homepage and product listing pages — these drive the most initial impressions</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span>Audit CLS on product detail pages — accidental taps on shifting "Add to Cart" buttons hurt conversion directly</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span>Minimize INP in the checkout flow — slow responses during purchase steps increase abandonment</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-blue-200 border-l-4 border-l-blue-500">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Mobile first</h3>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span>Google indexes and ranks the mobile version of your site — CWV on mobile directly affects search visibility</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span>Test on real mid-range devices (e.g. Moto G Power in DevTools throttling), not just fast desktop machines</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span>CrUX data on the Performance Overview page is broken down by device type when sufficient data is available</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-purple-200 border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Measure before and after</h3>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-500 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span>Capture a Lighthouse baseline before each optimization sprint so you can quantify the improvement</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-500 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span>Allow 4–6 weeks after launch before comparing CrUX field data — it represents a 28-day rolling average</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-500 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
            <span>Track Search Console "Core Web Vitals" report alongside conversion metrics to see correlated changes</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</AdminLayout>
